---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { t } from '../lib/i18n';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" width="narrow">
  <article class="about">
    <h1>About learncivicsense.in</h1>
    <p class="lede">{t('siteTagline')}</p>

    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      A free reading library for civic sense in India. Short lessons, drawn from everyday
      public-space situations: roads, transport, queues, markets, monuments, and the internet. No
      login. No accounts. No ads.
    </p>

    <h2>Who this is for</h2>
    <p>
      Adults and students in Indian cities, plus first-time travellers and returning NRIs. The
      lessons assume you are a thoughtful person who has not yet had the conversation in front of
      you.
    </p>

    <h2>What this is not</h2>
    <p>
      A lecture. A moral scoring system. A government tract. There are no quizzes with grades, no
      streaks, no points. The reading is the entire product.
    </p>

    <h2>How the content is built</h2>
    <p>
      Each lesson is written from a real Indian situation, cross-checked against published sources
      (government rules, peer-reviewed research, civic-society reports), and edited for plain
      language. Sources are linked at the bottom of every lesson.
    </p>

    <h2>Roadmap</h2>
    <p>
      The launch covers Traffic and Public Transport. The next phases add the other 9 categories,
      Hindi versions, and the other 6 Indian languages.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .about h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .about .lede {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }
  .about p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
</style>
